Today was rough just after 11 I got the dreaded call flashing the schools number and I knew immediately , I answered and I could hear Michael screaming in the back , Michael is not a big crier he could moan for Ireland but he is not one of those absolute hysterical criers , so I don't think she finished her sentence and I was in the car , I got to him I'm less then 2mins and I knew immediately by his colour alone it was bad , Michael fainted in the school yard during playtime he has no recollection of it he just remembers his eyes went black .. 

His daddy came home from work and my mother in law came and collected me and brought us in , with covid it's scary in there but anyway x-rays done and two very clear and visable breaks just above his wrist , orthopedic nurses came and set it in a moulded cast and he was x-rayed again , much to our disappointment the bones didn't set so it was phase 2 , sedation and the head orthopedic surgeon came down and pulled and popped the bones into place , Michael as ever never loosing his humor pulled of the sedation mask and said to the surgeon " exuse me I'm just letting you know your hurting me " the surgeon continued Michael " did you hear me I said your hurting me " 
He then shouted oh man I can see two of him but that's ok it's only because I no glasses on !! 

This kid breaks my heart and fills it with joy all at the same time , I'm broken that yet again were in this position , and again my concerns seem to me shrugged aside , just when we are going places 

But I'll get the answers..

For now we will be giving lots of TLC , he has earned many Robucks and a day of mom and dad have to say yes to anything challenge (Thanks @youtube )

